- Ah, some things.

19:34.840 --> 19:36.850
Most of it was just written
about the witch trials,

19:36.850 --> 19:38.860
which is pretty overplayed
'cause that's all

19:38.860 --> 19:40.460
Salem is known for.

19:40.460 --> 19:42.550
- Speaking of the Salem Witch Trials,

19:42.550 --> 19:43.530
the place where I grew up,

19:43.530 --> 19:45.990
it had a town called Hexi
and it was actually famous

19:45.990 --> 19:47.400
for its witch.

19:47.400 --> 19:50.040
So apparently when this
little girl was growing up,

19:50.040 --> 19:52.460
her parents died and they
used to play doctor with her.

19:52.460 --> 19:54.950
So I don't really know what that means.

19:54.950 --> 19:58.280
But later on, as she
grew up, she, thank you.

19:58.280 --> 19:59.113
- Thank you.

20:00.440 --> 20:03.630
- She became a witch
and she cursed the land.

20:03.630 --> 20:07.180
And actually this one family
died from drinking, the water,

20:07.180 --> 20:10.800
the rabbits, the squirrels,
everything was poisoned.

20:10.800 --> 20:13.050
And later the constable
found her in her house

20:13.050 --> 20:15.100
with maggots in her head.

20:15.100 --> 20:17.360
So yeah, that's where I grew up.

20:17.360 --> 20:18.700
- I feel like you've been drinking

20:18.700 --> 20:20.910
just a little too much, Skylar.

20:20.910 --> 20:22.050
- No, I'm serious.

20:22.050 --> 20:23.480
This happened.

20:23.480 --> 20:26.160
- Well, if it is true,
hopefully there's a book on it,

20:26.160 --> 20:27.460
'Cause I'd like to read about it

20:27.460 --> 20:30.270
'cause that sounds right up my alley.

20:30.270 --> 20:31.341
- What a nerd.

20:31.341 --> 20:32.980
(all laugh)

20:32.980 --> 20:34.340
- Actually, this is really good.

20:34.340 --> 20:35.960
Good suggestion, Sky.

20:35.960 --> 20:37.220
- You're welcome.

20:37.220 --> 20:39.040
- Piper, we have another surprise for you.

20:39.040 --> 20:41.950
- What? You guys have
already outdone yourselves

20:41.950 --> 20:43.650
with all this birthday stuff.

20:43.650 --> 20:45.090
- Well, if you don't want the surprise,

20:45.090 --> 20:47.610
we'll just go to the mall
and spend it on ourselves.

20:47.610 --> 20:48.600
- No, no.

20:48.600 --> 20:49.850
What is it already?

20:49.850 --> 20:50.920
- Okay. Okay.

20:50.920 --> 20:52.580
Are you ready?
- Yes.

20:52.580 --> 20:54.130
- Lilly, will you do the honor?

20:55.020 --> 20:57.750
- So Piper, we are taking
you for a palm reading

20:57.750 --> 21:00.200
at this new psychic over on 14th Ave.

21:00.200 --> 21:02.050
She's supposed to be the best around,

21:02.050 --> 21:03.653
and she moved here from Ireland.

21:04.540 --> 21:05.480
- Jesus Christ.

21:05.480 --> 21:08.413
I hope it's not that gook, Madam Sapphire.

21:08.413 --> 21:10.860
- What the hell does her
moving here from Ireland

21:10.860 --> 21:12.950
have to do with her being the best around?

21:12.950 --> 21:15.750
I mean, who the fuck
reads palms in Ireland?

21:15.750 --> 21:17.900
- Well, Miss Know It
All, it just so happens

21:17.900 --> 21:21.100
that all the best palm readers
originate from Ireland.

21:21.100 --> 21:22.810
I read it in a book once.

21:22.810 --> 21:23.933
- Of course you did.

21:24.780 --> 21:27.680
Guys, what does it matter
where she came from?

21:27.680 --> 21:30.630
I'm just excited to get my fortune told.

21:30.630 --> 21:32.249
- I knew you'd love that.

21:32.249 --> 21:35.332
(upbeat rock music)

21:37.363 --> 21:38.626
It's a real umbrella.

21:38.626 --> 21:40.371
(all laugh)

21:40.371 --> 21:43.204
(hard rock music)

23:07.047 --> 23:09.880
(mystical music)

23:17.390 --> 23:19.380
- Yeah, fuck this.

23:19.380 --> 23:20.790
- Oh no, you don't.

23:20.790 --> 23:21.910
This is Piper's present

23:21.910 --> 23:24.360
and you're going to stick
with us until the end.

23:24.360 --> 23:27.380
- How did you even hear
about this place again?

23:27.380 --> 23:30.600
- I saw a flyer at the Chinese
restaurant outside yesterday.

23:30.600 --> 23:33.030
- Thank God it wasn't
a flyer for a circus.

23:33.030 --> 23:35.730
Don't even look at it like
anyone's even working here.

23:38.010 --> 23:40.420
- Who has come to see Madam Sapphire?

23:40.420 --> 23:42.663
- Oh, Christ.

23:43.660 --> 23:47.093
- There's no taking the Lord's
name in vain in this house.

23:50.575 --> 23:52.930
(mystical music)

23:52.930 --> 23:55.280
- You better not ruin
Piper's birthday present.

23:57.080 --> 24:00.668
- Come this way, young
ladies, and enter my chamber.

24:00.668 --> 24:03.501
(mystical music)

24:21.828 --> 24:23.411
Have a seat ladies.

24:40.980 --> 24:44.680
So girls, let me tell you
a little bit about myself.

24:44.680 --> 24:49.680
I was born in Ireland in the
middle of a beautiful meadow.

24:51.180 --> 24:52.970
My mother knew I was gonna be special

24:52.970 --> 24:56.523
because a morning star shot
from the sky that morning.

24:57.820 --> 25:01.870
I always knew all kinds of things.

25:01.870 --> 25:06.080
And I knew when my
mother was going to pass

25:06.080 --> 25:09.170
and I really didn't want to tell her that.

25:09.170 --> 25:12.133
So I hopped the plane
and I came to the U.S.

25:13.010 --> 25:15.310
and that's why I'm here today,

25:15.310 --> 25:16.948
to help people in distress.

25:16.948 --> 25:19.781
(mystical music)

25:24.470 --> 25:27.833
So Piper, I hear it's your birthday.

25:29.040 --> 25:32.290
- Um, I'm Piper, Madam Sapphire.

25:32.290 --> 25:34.370
- Shouldn't you have known that?

25:36.310 --> 25:39.823
- Well, do you girls have
your cell phones on you?

25:40.700 --> 25:41.653
- [All] Yeah.

25:42.580 --> 25:45.350
- It's scrambling my psychic signals.

25:45.350 --> 25:47.720
So you really need to turn
them off and hand them to me

25:47.720 --> 25:49.770
so I can put them in the lobby.

25:49.770 --> 25:51.763
- What, you mean your living room?

25:53.601 --> 25:55.684
(sighs)

26:01.130 --> 26:01.963
- Thank you.

26:09.068 --> 26:11.901
(phones clatter)

26:16.513 --> 26:19.763
So young Piper, let me see your hand.

26:24.090 --> 26:27.283
Ooh, your heart line is very strong.

26:27.283 --> 26:28.890
(ominous music)

26:28.890 --> 26:30.208
But your lifeline...

26:30.208 --> 26:32.519
(gasps)

26:32.519 --> 26:34.656
- What?

26:34.656 --> 26:37.570
(sighs)

26:37.570 --> 26:39.903
- Let's just move on to the tarot cards.

26:47.510 --> 26:49.513
Shuffle the cards please, Piper.

27:05.010 --> 27:06.133
Card one.

27:08.890 --> 27:09.913
The rainbow.

27:12.270 --> 27:15.520
Happiness, joy pleasure,

27:15.520 --> 27:17.960
peace and contentment.

27:17.960 --> 27:20.343
Sounds like a wonderful start to your day.

27:22.240 --> 27:23.073
The hangman.

27:25.920 --> 27:30.920
Transition, change and
reversal of one's way of life.

27:36.950 --> 27:38.443
The falling tower.

27:43.290 --> 27:45.083
Sudden change,

27:46.380 --> 27:50.823
abandonment and end of long friendships.

27:58.437 --> 28:01.210
(ominous music)

28:01.210 --> 28:02.043
The devil.

28:06.330 --> 28:08.820
- What? Why are you
looking at me that way?

28:08.820 --> 28:11.070
- Yeah, come on guys.
This place is bullshit.

28:12.808 --> 28:15.800
(ominous music)

28:15.800 --> 28:18.710
- Wait, you have to listen to me!

28:18.710 --> 28:20.563
You're in grave danger!

28:21.550 --> 28:23.613
- Get off of me, you crazy bitch!

28:38.410 --> 28:40.260
- Wait girls, you forgot your phones.

28:42.150 --> 28:43.693
Please be careful.

28:44.548 --> 28:47.465
(children playing)

29:02.920 --> 29:05.230
- Thank God we're away
from that psychic bitch.

29:05.230 --> 29:07.430
- I know, we came here for a good time

29:07.430 --> 29:10.750
and she tries to soil our
evening with a black cloud.

29:10.750 --> 29:11.890
- How you feeling, Pipes?

29:11.890 --> 29:13.780
- I'm okay.

29:13.780 --> 29:15.960
How long till we get to Salem?

29:15.960 --> 29:17.290
- Well, the band starts at nine,

29:17.290 --> 29:18.620
so we've gotta get on the road now

29:18.620 --> 29:21.012
because we have dinner yet to go.

29:21.012 --> 29:23.679
(upbeat music)

30:22.580 --> 30:24.590
- [Piper] Guys, I really
don't know how to thank you

30:24.590 --> 30:26.090
for such an amazing birthday.

30:26.090 --> 30:28.380
- Aw, oh, you're so welcome.

30:28.380 --> 30:29.490
How has the pedi?

30:29.490 --> 30:31.960
- Oh God, it was the
most relaxing experience

30:31.960 --> 30:34.720
I've had in forever and
the lady, she was so nice.

30:34.720 --> 30:37.010
She hooked me up with
a pumpkin spice latte

30:37.010 --> 30:38.660
and an apple cider donut.

30:38.660 --> 30:41.490
- No way, a foot massage and a free latte?

30:41.490 --> 30:42.893
Sign me up for that shit.

30:43.810 --> 30:45.793
- Sounds like a daydream to me.

30:46.980 --> 30:48.010
- Well, you better take notes

30:48.010 --> 30:49.840
because my birthday's in a few months,

30:49.840 --> 30:53.573
but instead of pumpkin spice,
I want peppermint schnapps.

30:56.260 --> 30:58.110
- Well, I really can't believe you guys

30:58.110 --> 30:59.700
got us tickets for the show tonight.

30:59.700 --> 31:01.610
It's going to be a blast.

31:01.610 --> 31:04.960
- I cannot wait to see Marshall
and have him sing to me.

31:04.960 --> 31:06.760
He's so fucking hot.

31:06.760 --> 31:09.450
- You didn't happen to get
us backstage passes, did you?

31:09.450 --> 31:12.550
- No, the 33rd row was
the best I could do.

31:12.550 --> 31:16.110
- That's cool. I'll take
them any way I can get them.

31:16.110 --> 31:18.519
- Hey guys, who's getting hungry?

31:18.519 --> 31:19.436
- [All] Me!

31:21.244 --> 31:23.911
(gentle music)

31:56.240 --> 31:59.117
- You're a sinner and you know it.

31:59.117 --> 32:01.543
You don't follow what's in here.

32:03.230 --> 32:05.433
You have man on man sex.

32:06.840 --> 32:07.673
Abortions.

32:08.730 --> 32:09.883
You kill babies.

32:10.780 --> 32:12.633
You do drugs and alcohol.

32:14.560 --> 32:16.183
You vote for the wrong side.

32:18.240 --> 32:19.283
That's what you do.

32:21.120 --> 32:22.203
Sacrifice.

32:23.980 --> 32:25.860
Rainbows.

32:25.860 --> 32:27.013
Serpents.

32:28.320 --> 32:29.550
Are these things we need?

32:29.550 --> 32:31.748
- What is he talking about?
- Or things we just want?

32:31.748 --> 32:34.148
- I can't believe they
play this in restaurants.

32:35.910 --> 32:38.003
- You're a sinner and you know it.

32:38.003 --> 32:38.836
- You're a sinner

32:38.836 --> 32:39.753
and you know it.
- Because you don't follow

32:39.753 --> 32:41.323
- I know.
- what's in here.

32:42.470 --> 32:43.570
- Well, according to the internet,

32:43.570 --> 32:45.530
everything here's supposed to be amazing.

32:45.530 --> 32:48.060
- I know, I love places like this.

32:48.060 --> 32:49.490
- Small town charm, you know.
- These are things

32:49.490 --> 32:51.713
that are only going to hurt you.

32:51.713 --> 32:52.580
'Cause you're a sinner.

32:52.580 --> 32:54.530
- Don't even tell me.
- Mm-hmm.

32:54.530 --> 32:57.040
Mr. Smith himself.

32:57.040 --> 32:58.640
- I thought you were done with Nick.

32:58.640 --> 33:02.723
- I was, but we've just been
together for so long, you know.

33:03.710 --> 33:05.510
- What do they even want this time?

33:05.510 --> 33:07.090
- He's been after me all day

33:07.090 --> 33:08.580
to go out tonight for my birthday.

33:08.580 --> 33:11.110
But I said I had plans with the girls

33:11.110 --> 33:13.303
and he's been texting me all day.

33:14.990 --> 33:18.507
- [Preacher] Why do you
think that these are sins?

33:18.507 --> 33:22.523
These are people who should be cast out.

33:22.523 --> 33:24.273
Don't you understand?

33:25.590 --> 33:26.568
I don't think...

33:26.568 --> 33:28.218
- Is that what you want to drink?

33:29.450 --> 33:31.280
- I'll have a diet cola.

33:31.280 --> 33:32.980
I'll have a regular cola.

33:32.980 --> 33:34.360
- I'll have a diet as well.

33:34.360 --> 33:36.010
- Can I just have water?
- Sure.

33:37.460 --> 33:39.380
- [Preacher] I'm just being
(indistinct) from sin.

33:39.380 --> 33:42.300
- Guys, she scared the shit out of me.

33:42.300 --> 33:43.780
- Well online said the food was great

33:43.780 --> 33:45.830
but they didn't say
anything about the service.

33:45.830 --> 33:47.070
- Well maybe I'll hop online

33:47.070 --> 33:48.693
and give them a little feedback.

33:52.000 --> 33:55.210
- Oh man, look at all these choices.

33:55.210 --> 33:57.400
Biscuits and gravy is calling my name,

33:57.400 --> 33:59.800
but I think I'm actually gonna get

33:59.800 --> 34:01.310
a ham and cheese sandwich.

34:01.310 --> 34:03.814
- Biscuits and gravy at this hour?

34:03.814 --> 34:04.840
Gross.

34:04.840 --> 34:06.210
- Hey, she's a big girl.

34:06.210 --> 34:08.530
She can order what she wants.

34:08.530 --> 34:11.332
- I think I'm getting a corn dog.

34:11.332 --> 34:14.332
(preacher rambling)

34:17.949 --> 34:21.272
- [Preacher] If you can tell me

34:21.272 --> 34:25.052
what's truly wrong with this world...

34:25.052 --> 34:27.796
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

34:27.796 --> 34:30.658
- Thanks.
- You gotta sacrifice.

34:30.658 --> 34:32.480
- Thank you.

34:32.480 --> 34:35.920
- Do you guys know what you'd like to eat?

34:35.920 --> 34:38.060
- Um, yes, I'm gonna have

34:38.060 --> 34:40.230
the ham and cheese sandwich

34:40.230 --> 34:43.240
with beer-battered fries, please.

34:43.240 --> 34:46.440
- I'll have a cheeseburger
with onion rings.

34:46.440 --> 34:47.720
- What do you want on your burger?

34:47.720 --> 34:49.695
- Ah, ketchup and mustard.

34:49.695 --> 34:51.021
(preacher rambling)

34:51.021 --> 34:53.612
- I'll have the chicken sandwich
with beer-battered fries.

34:53.612 --> 34:55.153
- Bread or a roll?

34:55.153 --> 34:55.986
- Bread.

34:57.800 --> 35:02.800
- Can I have a corn dog and a side of

35:06.790 --> 35:07.663
mushrooms?

35:08.535 --> 35:09.368
- You got it.

35:12.697 --> 35:15.697
(preacher rambles)

35:24.096 --> 35:25.378
- Guys, there's this frame over there

35:25.378 --> 35:27.520
of this couple that says
customer of the month.

35:27.520 --> 35:29.070
I wonder what that's all about.

35:31.460 --> 35:33.580
- Hey, it's my birthday.

35:33.580 --> 35:36.100
Can I be the customer of the month today?

35:36.100 --> 35:37.330
- No.

35:37.330 --> 35:40.530
- So how do you become
customer of the month?

35:40.530 --> 35:42.750
- Whoever comes in the most
during the month previous

35:42.750 --> 35:44.256
is customer of the month.

35:44.256 --> 35:46.000
Graham and Emma are in
here almost every day,

35:46.000 --> 35:48.804
having tea and biscuits for breakfast.

35:48.804 --> 35:50.839
- Ooh, all right.

35:50.839 --> 35:53.756
(preacher rambles)

35:55.208 --> 35:57.625
(all laugh)

36:02.190 --> 36:03.880
- Why did you bring that with you?

36:03.880 --> 36:05.754
- Because it's a real umbrella.

36:05.754 --> 36:07.970
(all laugh)

36:07.970 --> 36:08.803
- [Preacher] You're
gonna go straight to hell

36:08.803 --> 36:10.200
at this point.
- Yeah,

36:10.200 --> 36:11.033
- And you'll deserve it.
- Maddie.

36:11.033 --> 36:12.178
You're gonna go straight to hell.

36:12.178 --> 36:13.280
(all laugh)

36:13.280 --> 36:17.160
- I'm really going to hell if
you can't have even one drink.

36:17.160 --> 36:19.433
- Right, we were just at the strip club.

36:23.900 --> 36:26.299
- What brings you girls to town today?

36:26.299 --> 36:28.290
- Oh, just going to a concert.

36:28.290 --> 36:29.460
- Concert?

36:29.460 --> 36:31.600
There's nothing going on around here.

36:31.600 --> 36:32.480
- It's in Salem.

36:32.480 --> 36:35.590
You see, we're all going
together for her birthday.

36:35.590 --> 36:37.400
- Oh, which way are you headed?

36:37.400 --> 36:40.310
- Um, North 33.

36:40.310 --> 36:42.100
About two hours away from here.

36:42.100 --> 36:45.050
- Well, whatever you do, you
make sure you stay on 33.

36:45.050 --> 36:46.410
Don't take any shortcuts

36:46.410 --> 36:48.660
and don't go on School House Road.

36:48.660 --> 36:50.960
You don't wanna end up there. Trust me.

36:50.960 --> 36:51.950
Enjoy your meal.

36:51.950 --> 36:54.200
- [Preacher] His house, you
don't follow the rules...

36:54.200 --> 36:55.869
- What was that all about?

36:55.869 --> 36:57.137
- I don't know.

36:57.137 --> 36:58.839
(preacher rambles)

36:58.839 --> 37:01.884
(ketchup squirts)

37:01.884 --> 37:03.365
- Hey guys. Mm.

37:03.365 --> 37:05.698
(all laugh)

37:07.512 --> 37:08.345
- Funny.

37:10.450 --> 37:11.343
- [Preacher] That's a sin.

37:13.385 --> 37:14.323
Your life is...

37:14.323 --> 37:16.593
- That was a really good home-cooked meal.

37:17.430 --> 37:21.920
- Now all I need is a tall glass of vodka.

37:21.920 --> 37:23.673
- That's the last thing you need.

37:25.010 --> 37:27.680
- It feels like we've been
waiting for this check forever.

37:27.680 --> 37:30.460
- No wonder, she's all over
that guy in the corner.

37:30.460 --> 37:33.020
- [Waitress] Pay attention to me.

37:33.020 --> 37:34.830
- Um, excuse me?

37:34.830 --> 37:36.923
Could we please have our check?

37:38.346 --> 37:41.263
(preacher rambles)

37:43.958 --> 37:44.791
- Thanks.

37:54.719 --> 37:55.820
- Now remember what I said.

37:55.820 --> 37:57.920
You guys wanna stay off School House Road.

37:59.067 --> 37:59.900
- Thanks.

38:01.660 --> 38:02.900
- Well, we better get going.

38:02.900 --> 38:05.470
I'm not going to miss Marshall
singing his love songs

38:05.470 --> 38:06.463
without a shirt on.

38:07.301 --> 38:09.009
- I know he's so dreamy.

38:09.009 --> 38:11.676
(ominous music)

38:13.495 --> 38:16.328
(crickets chirp)

38:21.660 --> 38:24.320
- Well there's still some
travel time left in the trip.

38:24.320 --> 38:27.310
We might as well play a
game of truth or dare.

38:27.310 --> 38:29.760
- What? How are we gonna
do dares in the car?

38:29.760 --> 38:32.810
- Okay then. Truth, truth.

38:32.810 --> 38:34.443
- I don't know about that guys.

38:35.583 --> 38:37.596
- Why, do you have something to hide?

38:37.596 --> 38:38.470
- Ha, ha.

38:38.470 --> 38:40.713
We all know you have nothing to hide.

38:45.040 --> 38:46.470
Well, who's gonna go first?

38:46.470 --> 38:47.870
- Oh, me, me.

38:47.870 --> 38:49.940
- Okay, Piper. You can go first.

38:49.940 --> 38:51.920
- Piper, have you ever smoked weed?

38:51.920 --> 38:54.510
- (scoffs) Who hasn't?

38:54.510 --> 38:58.910
- Uh-oh, somebody better
call Rehab Anonymous.

38:58.910 --> 39:02.350
- It's Alcoholics Anonymous, genius.

39:02.350 --> 39:05.270
- Oh, okay. Act like you never did.

39:05.270 --> 39:06.830
- Okay. Okay.

39:06.830 --> 39:08.310
Who's next?

39:08.310 --> 39:09.273
- Me, do me.

39:10.190 --> 39:11.610
- Okay, Lilly.

39:11.610 --> 39:14.263
Have you ever stolen a
book from the library?

39:15.270 --> 39:18.620
- Why would I do that when
I can rent them for free?

39:18.620 --> 39:21.620
- I don't know what kind of
twisted book fantasies you have.

39:22.500 --> 39:23.960
- Good Lord, Skylar. All right.

39:23.960 --> 39:25.450
It's your turn.

39:25.450 --> 39:26.980
- Okay. Hit me.

